    <fr:title text="Cartesian Product">Cartesian Product</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>The cartesian product is a binary operation defined between two sets, that produces a set of all ordered pairs from the arguments.</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\set {a,b,c,...}\times \set {\alpha ,\beta ,\gamma ,...}=\Set {(a,\alpha ),(a,\beta ),(a,\gamma ),...,(b,\alpha ),(b,\beta ),(b,\gamma ),...}]]></fr:tex>
    <html:p>or</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[A\times  B=\set {All\; ordered\; pairs\; of A\;and\;B}]]></fr:tex>
    <html:p>Note: Since the cartesian product is a set, we are not limited to only creating binary operations. We can go to arbitrarily higher orders.</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[A\times  B\times  C\times  D]]></fr:tex>
  </fr:mainmatter>
